<div class="container mt-4 privacy-container">
    <h1>NMC Privacy Statement</h1>
    <p>
        Northwestern Michigan College (NMC) operates several public websites including <strong>nmc.edu</strong>, <strong>wnmc.org</strong> and <strong>dennosmuseum.org</strong>.
        It is our intention to respect your privacy regarding any information we may collect while you are visiting our websites.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <h2>Our Commitment To Privacy</h2>
    <p>
        Your privacy is important to us. To better protect your privacy, we provide this notice explaining our online information practices and
        the choices you can make about the way your information is collected and used.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <h2>The Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>
        This notice applies to information collected or submitted on the NMC, WNMC and Dennos websites listed above.
    </p>
    <p>Information about your use of these websites is collected using server access logs and tracking cookies. The collected information consists of the following:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>The IP address from which you access the website</li>
        <li>The type of browser and operating system you use to access our site</li>
        <li>The date and time you access our site</li>
        <li>The pages you visit</li>
        <li>The addresses of pages from where you followed a link to our site</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        The tracking cookies track anonymous data and are set by Google Analytics and handled by Google as described in
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">Google's privacy policy</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
        We also use a tool called Microsoft Clarity to gather information regarding visitors to our public website at <strong>nmc.edu</strong>.
        Learn more about Clarity’s data collection and use <a href="https://clarity.microsoft.com/" target="_blank">here</a>.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <h2>Personal Information You Provide</h2>
    <p>On some pages, you may provide the following types of personal information:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Name</li>
        <li>Address</li>
        <li>Email address</li>
        <li>Phone number</li>
        <li>Credit Card Information (not stored by NMC)</li>
    </ul>

    <hr />

    <h2>The Ways We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We use the information that you provide about yourself only to complete your request. We do not share this information with outside parties except to the extent necessary to complete the request.</p>
    <p>Return email addresses are only used to respond to inquiries and are not shared or used for other purposes.</p>

    <hr />

    <h2>Our Commitment To Data Security</h2>
    <p>We use appropriate physical, electronic, and managerial procedures to safeguard and secure the information we collect online.</p>

    <hr />

    <h2>Privacy Statement Changes</h2>
    <p>NMC may change its Privacy Statement at any time. Please check this page regularly for updates. Continued use of this site indicates acceptance of any changes.</p>

    <hr />

    <h2>Accessing or Correcting Your Info</h2>
    <p>You can access and correct your personal information by contacting us directly. We will verify your identity before granting access or making corrections.</p>

    <hr />

    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>
        To be removed from mailing lists for print publications, email:
        <a href="mailto:foundation@nmc.edu">foundation@nmc.edu</a>
        or call (877) 922-1021 / (231) 995-1021.
    </p>
    <p>
        For questions about personal information on our websites, email:
        <a href="mailto:publicrelations@nmc.edu">publicrelations@nmc.edu</a> or call (231) 995-1020.
    </p>

    <p><em>Last updated March 24, 2023</em></p>
</div>
